                        <interp inst="t18800913-name-172" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY SIMS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a clicker of 6, Duncan Street, Hackney—about I a.m. on Sunday, the 29th August, I was in the Bethnal Green Road—I saw Allen and another man in conversation—the other man threw me on my back in the middle of the road, the prisoner got on my chest, put his hand on my mouth so that I could not breathe, the other one rifled my pockets</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="188009130045"></xptr>
               <p>and took away 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 1 1/2 <hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—I cried out "Police" as soon as I could and two constables came and took the prisoner off—I have spit blood, attended the hospital, and have been ill ever since, and kept from work in consequence of the doctor's instructions.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
